He died a most holy death, surrounded by Dr. Power‚ his con- fessor, and two Sisters of Mercy, on the 4th of August, 1878. His last words were “ My God, accept the sacrifice of my life.’' His remains were conveyed to Ireland to be buried in his own Diocese of Ardagh.

Before they were taken to Longford‚ they were placed in the Cathedral, Marlborough-street‚ Dubfin, where a solemn office -and High Mass were celebrated for the repose of his soul, in presence of Cardinal Cullen‚ who presided, other prelates and several clergy. Afterwards they were removed to his own cathedra] at Longford, whither came several bishops‚ the priests of Ardagh, and many from the adjoining Sees, to take part in the funeral obsequies.
